div.h1: Figure 2: The Geology of Capital Creation

h1.p: The easiest way to understand the functional creation and control of capital is in terms of 'geological' layers. The Production Layer, at the bottom, does not require the other layers in order to operate as a market driven economy. However, on its own it cannot compete with a capital geology. Whilst individual businesses are rendered less competitive from capital extraction, as long as the resource is transferred to promising supply chains via capital investment, businesses inside the same supply chain will struggle to compete and hence survive.
